{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778268028,"nonce":"ap6Mz62p9oaf8BlkpCa2IJYiGns=","message":"## C\u0026S 2019 analytical re-review (Stage 0 follow-up)\n\nA re-review of cs2019.pdf (full report: /tmp/flavor_ab_review/findings/cs2019_review.md) identified two structural gaps in our analytical Riccati setup. New issue: 9a0558e (8-state plant lift + 50ms delay augmentation).\n\n## Motivation\n\nThe phase umbrella f695729 originally framed the Δv puzzle as: trained ≈ -25%, analytical ≈ +1-2%, C\u0026S ≈ +10-15% (visual). The re-review:\n1. Established that C\u0026S never report a numerical Δv in the paper text — the +10-15% number was a visual estimate from Fig 1e. User has now measured Fig 1e directly: 125 vs 116 px → +7.76%.\n2. Identified that our analytical setup is structurally incomplete relative to C\u0026S 2019 + the released ModelDB code (258846).\n\n## Hypotheses (named, with disposition)\n\n- **G1 — 50ms (5-step) sensorimotor delay augmentation.** Trained side has it (feedback_delay_steps=5); analytical does not. C\u0026S analytical implements it via shift-register state augmentation. Real and untested. **Strong second.**\n- **G2 — Kalman state estimator.** C\u0026S use estimated state in their pipeline overall, but the released analytical Riccati code runs on the augmented state directly without a Kalman in the H∞ recursion. Not a gap for the analytical figure. **Defer.**\n- **G3 — Numerical Δv from C\u0026S text.** C\u0026S never report numerical Δv; text quotes are about cost (~15% higher robust cost, \u003c20% vs ~30% perturbation cost increase, p.8139). **Disproven as a target.** Reframe success metric to user-measured +7.76% from Fig 1e + cost-based comparisons.\n- **G4 — Cost-schedule scaling.** Absolute weight values, not just (t/N)^6 shape. Matches on shared 6 entries. **Trivial extension after G6.**\n- **G5 — Horizon mismatch.** C\u0026S 600ms; we use 800ms. **Deprioritized per user.**\n- **G6 — 8-state plant with disturbance-integrator coupling.** C\u0026S: states 7,8 are pure integrators driven by D=I_8, with A[3,7]=A[4,8]=1 coupling integrated disturbance INTO velocity. We use B_w=I_6 applied directly. Structurally different H∞ game (smooth cumulative drift vs impulsive noise). **Load-bearing gap.**\n- **G7 — Motor/system noise (α₂, α₃).** Not active in published-figure analytical run; also averaged out across 100 sims per Fig 1e legend. **Not a gap.**\n\n## Conclusion\n\nG6 + G1 are the operative gaps. New rlrmp issue 9a0558e implements both as a structural lift to cs_faithful_pointmass. Stage 0 of umbrella f695729 (issue 03a148a) gets this as a sub-task.\n\nReframed Δv target: +7.76% (user-measured Fig 1e). Synthesis update pending.\n\nStatus: exploring, not committed.","files":null}]}